condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section G | Description :Recipient shall ensure that from FY2008/09, the government budgetaryallocation for road maintenance works for both local roads andstrategic roads will be consolidated and channeled through RBN. | DueDate :01-Jul-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section H.i | Description :Recipient shall cause RBN make decision by end FY07/08, which would allowsalary structure 2B competitive/similar to other autonomous boards in Nepal, in form & substance acceptable to IDA & Recipient |Due Date :01-Jul-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section H.ii | Description :Recipient shall cause RBN develop structured HR Dept. Plan for RBNincluding staff career development & training plan; & thereafterimplement such plan. | Due Date :30-Jun-2009

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.1 | Description :Recipient shall through DOR i)at least 60 days prior to the begining ofeach FY prepare and furnish to IDA proposed AWPB for such FY; & ii)afford IDA reasonable opportunity to discuss AWPB w/DOR. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.2 | Description :Recipient shall ensure AWPB includes adequate allocation of Recipient'sown funds to periodic maintenance of strategic highway& feeder road network. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A.1 | Description :Recipient shall maintain PCT within Foreign Cooperation Branch of DORwith adequate number of key professionals with skills, qualification, experience and TORs satisfactory to IDA. | Frequency :Monthly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A.2 | Description :Recipient shall maintain each PMU an adequate no. of key professionalswith skills, qualifications, experience and TORs satisfactory to IDA, including without limitation a Sr. Divisional Engineer. |Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.A.3 | Description :Recipient shall ensure key staff in the PCT/PMU listed Schedule 2,I.A.1 & 2 are not transferred to other positions during period Project implementation until 6 months following closing date. |Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.E | Description :Recipient shall submit to Parliament Secretariat for approval, draft ofan amendment to the Roads Board Nepal Act, 2058 (2002) satisfactory to IDA which will address RBN matters. | Due Date :31-Dec-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.F.i | Description :Recipient shall meet budget demand of RBN in each FY during theProject's implementation period for the purposes of providing fundsto DOR to carry out periodic maintenance. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.F.ii | Description :Recipient shall channel adequate funds to RBN for maintenance andoperating costs. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.F.iii | Description :Recipient shall by April 30 of each FY, develop annual spendingtargets for RBN that are acceptable to IDA. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I.F.iv) | Description :Recipient shall thereafter ensure that such annual spending targetsfor each FY are achieved. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section J.i | Description :Recipient shall develop standard satisfactory to IDA for calculatingpresent value DOR's assets and yearly depreciation thereof. | Due Date :30-Jun-2008

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section J.ii | Description :Recipient shall establish asset registers in each DOR's divisions forassets in such division that are valued at more than NPRs 1M. | Due Date :30-Sep-2009

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section J.iii | Description :Recipient shall update asset registers by Dec.31 of each FY includingbrief description of each asset, present value based on depreciation & additional costs that have been incurred on such asset. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section L.i | Description :Recipient shall develop for each DOR's unit business & resource plansatisfactory to IDA setting forth specific output requirementsfor following 3year period. | Due Date :30-Apr-2008
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section L.ii | Description :Recipient shall implement each such plan in a manner & with a timetablesatisfactory to IDA. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section M.i | Description :Recipient shall each FY carry out performance eval.of contractors &consultants engaged in accordance w/provisions of Public Procurement Act & rules promulgated thereunder. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section M.ii | Description :Recipient shall submit by end 1st quarter of succeeding FY, consolidatedreport of evals. including description actions taken against any contractor/consultant whose performance was less than satisfac |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule IV, Section B | Description :No withdrawal shall be made...for expenditures related todisbursement-linked results financed or agreed to be financed by the Association in accordance with the PforR Financing Agreementfor the Bridges Improvement and Maintennace Program. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS
